sentences: Lou Halmy (June 23, 1911 – March 14, 2005) was a jazz musician and music arranger.
In the 1930s he played trumpet with Shep Fields and His Rippling Rhythm Orchestra and appeared with the orchestra in the film The Big Broadcast of 1938.
